Date: Fri, 20 Mar 2026 16:53:56 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 027/174] =?UTF-8?q?PGCL:=20sessions=2035-36=20fixes=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20mincore,=20mmap,=20madvise,=20vDSO,=209p=20I/O?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Session 35 (all 5 arches 23/23 PASS):
- mincore: 7 fixes for MMUPAGE-granular page walking and vec output
- mmap: 5 fixes (stack_guard_gap, brk guard, shadow stack, low_limit)
- madvise: 2 fixes (populate stride, anon name alignment)
- util: 2 fixes (randomize_page, arch_mmap_rnd modulo MMUPAGE_SIZE)
- mm.h: 1 fix (vm_end_gap uses MMUPAGE_SIZE)

Session 36 (9p I/O corruption fix):
- iov_iter: GUP page counting and offset use MMUPAGE_SIZE
- netfs/iterator: bvec offset advancement by actual bytes consumed
- 9p/trans_virtio: pstep parameter distinguishes GUP vs bvec/folioq
  page granularity in scatter-gather list construction
- 9p/vfs_file: vm_pgoff uses MMUPAGE_SIZE

Additional arch fixes:
- arm64 crypto: MMUPAGE_SIZE for AES key struct, NH block alignment
- powerpc: vDSO layout, KVM rmhandlers, thread_info stack
- s390: boot vmem, KVM DAT/gaccess, fault handling, mmap, pageattr
- riscv: text patching fixmap MMUPAGE_SIZE
- x86 vDSO: layout linker script MMUPAGE offsets
- Generic TLB: gather page_size and flush stride fixes
- btrfs: compression workspace PAGE_SIZE annotation

Tested: x86_64, arm64, riscv64, s390x, ppc64 — all 23/23 PASS
Fedora x86_64 rootfs via 9p: gcc compile+run PASS

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
